    "closed_at": null,
    "body": "Just insert \".*\" before and after each character in :query.\r\n\r\nIn [lib/route.ls](https://github.com/g0v/laweasyread/blob/master/lib/route.ls), /api/suggestion/:query is now implemented as `collection.find { name: $elemMatch: { name: { $regex: keyword } } }` after `keyword = req.params.query`\r\n\r\nFor abbreviations are usually formed by picking up words in the full name, I think the regex could be simply written like `$regexText = \".*\" + implode(\".*\", str_split($keyword)) + \".*\";`\r\n(Here's in PHP since I'm only familiar with it. Documents are [implode()](http://tw2.php.net/manual/en/function.implode.php) and [str_split()](http://tw2.php.net/manual/en/function.str-split.php))\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n* \"兒童少年\" would be \".*兒.*童.*少.*年.*\" and therefore match those like \"[兒童及少年xxxxx](http://laweasyread.herokuapp.com/api/suggestion/%E5%85%92%E7%AB%A5%E5%8F%8A%E5%B0%91%E5%B9%B4)\"\r\n* \"通監法\" would be \".*通.*監.*法.*\" and therefore match \"通訊保障及監察法\""
